{
  "stem": "14897.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in my opinion, they had to be-- they had to make themselves very blind not to see--",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I am talking about civilians, though not necessarily just civilians.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It could be also the military.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because after all, the majority of the German military were not the SS, but were the Wehrmacht, the fighting soldiers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I think that there were so many camps in Germany, so many people who worked at the camps, obviously, they all talked.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Obviously, they talked to their families.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Obviously, this-- you really had to make a concerted effort to say, well, it's not my business.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I want to survive myself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Even though I'm a decent person, there's nothing I can do about it-- very much an attitude that most people take even today, in relation to other things that are obviously not as terrible as what was happening to the Jews, but trying not to see the-- the ills of society.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, now, we were liberated, as I told you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We're in that village the next day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I speak English, so I am able to communicate with the American soldiers and officers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- the Americans immediately sent some doctors.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because many people were in a terrible condition.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in fact, so pitifully, I remember one family that all died in that period because they were so starved, they were unable-- their stomachs were unable to-- to absorb food.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So here, to survive, and to die within the next few days.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father, being a doctor, was working in one of these little makeshift hospitals.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I, because I spoke English, was asked to go on the rounds with the American doctors who could not communicate with the patients.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
